title: America's Got Talent - Season 10
description:
A weekly talent competition where an array of performers -- from singers and dancers, to comedians and novelty acts -- vie for a $1 million cash prize.

Season ten of America's Got Talent premiered on May 26, 2015 and concluded on September 16, 2015. On July 29, the show aired a special two-hour tenth anniversary retrospective episode. The series returned to Radio City Music Hall in New York for the live shows, which began Tuesday, August 11. Dunkin' Donuts replaced Snapple as sponsor of the show after three seasons.

Nick Cannon returned as host for his seventh season. Howie Mandel returned for his sixth season as a judge while Mel B and Heidi Klum both returned for their third season on this panel. Howard Stern announced on his radio show that this, his fourth season, would be his last one as a judge due to a busy work schedule. Four guests were invited to judge during the judge's cuts; actor Neil Patrick Harris, singer Michael BublÃ©, actor Marlon Wayans and former judge Piers Morgan.
